<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF107-961-272  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 961 272.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Nov 28 1989* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Color plasma display due next spring.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Takahashi, Ken.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Matsushita Electronics Corp. (product development).andO;Topic:     Product DevelopmentGas Plasma Displays.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>COLOR PLASMA DISPLAY DUE NEXT SPRING OSAKA, JAPAN, 1989 NOV 20 (NB) --Matsushita Electronics will begin sample shipment of the world's firstmulticolor plasma display units as early as next spring.andM;The new 12-inch display will have a resolution of 400 by 640 pixels, and willbe capable of displaying about 4,000 colors and 16 shades of gray.andM;A plasma display is a flat display with sharper images than those on liquidcrystal displays.andP;  Demand is currently increasing for the orange-coloredplasma displays in office equipment, such as personal computers.andM;Matsushita Electronics started serious development on a multicolor plasmadisplay last year, and showed a prototype 17-inch unit in March of this year.andM;The price of the new display is unknown, but the firm promises to price itmuch lower than a similarly sized color LCD.andM;(Ken Takahashi/19891122)</TEXT></DOC>